  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer (M&E)",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p><ul><li>Be responsible for the planning, scheduling, controlling and coordinating of building services related works in terms of preventive / breakdown / A&A Works</li><li>To lead a team of supervisors & skilled workers to carry out their works accurately and timely and to ensure that works on site are carried out according to client requirement</li><li>Liaise and hold meetings with clients, Managing Agent & Sub contractor to ensure that all requirements by clients and relevant authorities are adhered</li><li>Monitor, track, and provide timely project progress reports to the management</li></ul><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least Bachelor's Degree/Post Graduate Diploma/Professional Degree in Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), project & facilities management, building services engineering, mechanical engineering or equivalent or equivalent.</li><li>Diploma holders with relevant facilities management, M&E experience are also welcome to apply</li><li>Good knowledge of M&E coordination</li><li>Electrical and ACMV design capability would be an added advantage</li><li>Committed, positive attitude & able to handle projects independently</li><li>Good team player with ability to lead and multi-task</li><li>At least 2 Year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position</li></ul>",
